                <pb facs="0456" n="434" xml:id="pg_434"/>
                <p>In a short plenary session, at which <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Molotov</hi>
                    presided, the agreements concerning the revision of the Italian armistice terms
                    were signed by the four Ministers (copy of revised terms attached).<note n="77" xml:id="d142fn77">The Revision of the Italian Armistice Terms, as approved
                        by the Council, was circulated as document <gloss target="#t_CFM461">C.F.M.
                            (46)</gloss> 95, May 16, 1946, <ref target="#pg_436">p.
                        436</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed that these were not to be made public until signed by the Allied
                    Commander-in-Chief and the Italian Government.<note n="78" xml:id="d142fn78">The
                        agreement was, in fact, never signed; for additional documentation on this
                        subject, see <ref target="frus1946v05#pg_825">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, pp. 825</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
